{'generation_mode': 'legacy', 'content': {'family_md': '## Target Models\n\n- Llama-3.2-3B-quantized.w8a8\n- Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct-FP8\n- Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct-AWQ\n\n# Llama 3.2\n\n## 1. Model Introduction\n\nLlama 3.2 is a collection of pretrained and instruction tuned generative models, released in July 2024 by Meta. These models are available in 8B, 70B and 405B sizes, with the 405B variant being the most capable fully-open source model at the time.\n\nThese models bring open intelligence to all, with several new features and improvements:\n\n- **Stronger General Intelligence**: These models showcase significant improvements in coding, state-of-the-art tool use, and overall stronger reasoning capabilities.\n- **Extended Context Length**: Llama 3.2 extends the context length to 128K tokens to improve performance over long context tasks such as summarization and code reasoning.\n- **Tool Use**: Llama 3.2 is trained to interact with a search engine, python interpreter and mathematical engine, and also improves zero-shot tool use capabilities to interact with potentially unseen tools.\n- **Multilinguality**: Llama 3.2 supports 7 languages in addition to English: French, German, Hindi, Italian, Portuguese, Spanish, and Thai.\n\nFor further details, please refer to the [Llama 3.2 blog](https://ai.meta.com/blog/meta-llama-3-2/) and the [Llama 3.2 model card](https://github.com/meta-llama/llama-models/blob/main/models/llama3_3_2/MODEL_CARD.md).note\n\n## 2. Model Acquisition\n\nYou can access the models on huggingface.\n\n| Data Type | Model Card |\n|:---:|:---:|\n| BF16 | [meta-llama/Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct](https://huggingface.co/meta-llama/Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct) |\n| W8A8_INT8 | [RedHatAI/Meta-Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct-quantized.w8a8](https://huggingface.co/RedHatAI/M\n\n<!-- REF_TRUNCATED: omitted 3860 chars -->\n\nom the dataset.\n- `--random-input 1024`, `--random-output 1024` and `--random-range-ratio 1.0` settings are for fixed 1024-in/1024-out token size limit (reali